“On the matter of gender-based violence, as with all matters of accountability with your government, you go from Mr Talk-a-lot, to Dr Do-little,” said interim leader of the DA John Steenhuisen to President Cyril Ramaphosa during a question-and-answer session in parliament on Thursday afternoon. Questions relating to Covid-19 corruption, gender-based violence and the appointment of Zandile Gumede to the KwaZulu-Natal legislature allowed for some heated debates in the house. Watch the video for four key points from the Q&A session. TimesLIVE